<subSubSection id="DCCBBC87FFC200436892FEEFFAE88C7D" pageId="41" pageNumber="542" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="946EEF0CFFC200436892FEEFFAE88C7D" blockId="41.[151,1437,315,522]" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC200436892FEEFFEE78F22" bold="true" box="[151,274,315,341]" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
SIF = 5B1N-N-2-3111.1000; fsp = 7.7.7; fCx = 1.1.1; fSt = 2.2; fPp = B/B/BBB; fSc: PL&gt; AM&gt; AL; Ip = 607–637; fD = 2H-6-6-6-4-4(6)-2; DS = 30–32; V = 26–30; NDV = 57–60. Palpal claw two-pronged, outer prong smaller; scutum nearly pentagonal, sparsely punctated, with distinct anterolateral shoulders, with angulate posterior margin; AM anterior to level of AL; sensilla flagelliform, with 8–10 branches in distal part, far anterior to level of PL (PSB—P-PL = 8–10 µm); sternal setae with few cilia or nude, coxal seta I with 2 branches, coxal seta II looks nude, coxal seta III with 3 branches. Standard measurements of examined specimens given in 
<tableCitation id="D953DAB7FFC200436CB0FE3BFAEC8C7D" box="[1205,1305,495,522]" captionStart="TABLE 15" captionStartId="41.[151,239,569,593]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="TABLE 15. Morphometric (AW–dmt, µm; m-t—ratio) and meristic (DS–NDV) traits of Microtrombicula paralios (n = 4)." pageId="41" pageNumber="542">Table 15</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
