<subSubSection id="DCCBBC87FFC2004368C2F85CFD1D899E" pageId="41" pageNumber="542" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="946EEF0CFFC2004368C2F85CFD1D899E" blockId="41.[151,1437,1711,2025]" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC2004368C2F85CFECE89D5" bold="true" box="[199,315,1928,1954]" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar, by all available characters, to 
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC200436BE9F853FB6E89D6" box="[1004,1179,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">Microtrombicul</emphasis>
a 
<taxonomicName id="53D1948FFFC200436CB4F853FEA289B1" authority="(Brennan and Jones, 1960)" baseAuthorityName="Brennan and Jones" baseAuthorityYear="1960" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fragibarba">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC200436CB4F853FADF89D6" box="[1201,1322,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">fragibarba</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F04092FDFFC200436D39F85CFEBA89B1" author="Brennan, J. M. &amp; Jones, E. K." pageId="41" pageNumber="542" pagination="493 - 540" refId="ref26170" refString="Brennan, J. M. &amp; Jones, E. K. (1960) Chiggers of Trinidad, BWI (Acarina: Trombiculidae). Acarologia, 2, 493 - 540." type="journal article" year="1960">Brennan and Jones, 1960</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter was described incompletely. A careful redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="53D1948FFFC200436C67F878FAF589B2" baseAuthorityName="Brennan and Jones" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[1122,1280,1963,1989]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="542" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fragibarba">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC200436C67F878FAF589B2" box="[1122,1280,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="542">M. fragibarba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is required to establish the possible conspecificity of these species.
</paragraph>
